The paper deals with interference mitigation in cognitive radio systems, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes new transmission schemes that utilize coding and relaying techniques, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper includes numerical simulations to illustrate the performance of the proposed schemes, which is related to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
